Commentary.Commentary: All in readiness now. Tom Latham and Will Young are the Kiwi openers. Kagiso Rabada to steam in...
... DAY 1, SESSION 3 ...

The South African players are back on the field. They are going through their warm-up drills at the moment. We're hearing that TEA has been taken on Day 1. Do join us in a short while then for the final session.
... SECOND INNINGS ...

Right then, the batting has let South Africa down and it's over to their bowlers to help them get back in this Test match. They have plenty of quality in their bowling ranks and let's see how they utilize the conditions. Stay tuned to find out...

The destroyer-in-chief, Matt Henry comes up for a quick chat. Says that it's a great start to the Test match and he is feeling great in front of his friends and family. Tells that it's nice to get an opportunity to play Test cricket. Mentions that after watching the overhead conditions, he was hoping to get a chance to bowl first.

South Africa were put to bat under testing conditions but by no means it's a 95 all out surface. There was a lack of application on their part and the technique was also questionable. They ended up playing many deliveries meant to be left and as a result, kept losing wickets. Zubayr Hamza and Kyle Verreynne did put up a little resistance but that was not enough.

Blown away! No strong wind here in Christchurch but the local boy, Matt Henry, has still blown away the Proteas with his stormy bowling. With an outstanding bowling figure of 7 for 23, the speedster decimated the South African batting line-up. The other bowlers also rallied around him and it was a clinical show from the Kiwis in the park.

OUT! TAKEN! This is on a driving length, outside off. Duanne Olivier is tempted and goes for it. Induces an outside edge to second slip where Tom Latham takes a low catch to his right. South Africa are bundled out for 95.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Latham b Neil Wagner

Commentary.Commentary: A yorker, on middle. Duanne Olivier gets his bat down to block it out.
Full ball, on middle, this is hit to mid on.
Slightly short and on off. Jansen defends it out.
On a length and on middle, Duanne Olivier tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Duanne Olivier looks to defend but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
A length ball, around off. Duanne Olivier misses his push. An appeal for caught behind as there was some noise but that might be off the bat brushing the pads.
FOUR BYES! Anti-climatic finish to the hat-trick delivery. A length ball, way outside off and shaping away. Left alone. The keeper fumbles and the ball rolls through the slip cordon for a boundary.
Matt Henry on a hat-trick...
Full and outside off. Marco leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Touch fuller, angling across and beating the outside edge of Jansen who looks to defend off the front foot.
A short one now, on middle. Marco sits under it.
On the pads, on a length. Jansen flicks it uppishly and past square leg for a couple of runs.
Full ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Fuller and on middle. Jansen blocks it out.
Duanne Olivier is the last batsman.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! The debutant goes for a golden duck and Matt Henry is on a hat-trick. Again it's a touch short and around off, it nips away a touch after landing. Glenton Stuurman is squared up as he looks to defend and a faint outside edge goes to the keeper who does the rest. The umpire takes some time before raising his dreaded finger. Matt Henry will have to wait for his hat-trick delivery though. A triple-wicket maiden for him!
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Blundell b Matt Henry

Commentary.Commentary: Debutant Glenton Stuurman is the new batter.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Matt Henry is not done yet and is eyeing to take all the remaining wickets now. The speedster comes from around the wicket and serves a shortish delivery outside off. Kagiso Rabada gets on his toes to defend but it takes the outside edge and flies to the keeper. Tom Blundell takes an easy catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Blundell b Matt Henry

Commentary.Commentary: A length ball, angling on the pads. Rabada fails to defend and gets hit high on the pads.
Fuller ball, slanting in, outside off. Rabada shoulders arms. Good leave.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Kagiso Rabada arrives next.

DRS time! A big shout for an lbw is turned down by the onfield umpire. Matt Henry successfully convinces his skipper to review the decision. Flat line on the UltraEdge and it's hitting the leg stump on the Ball Tracking. Matt Henry has five!

OUT! LBW! Matt Henry was very sure of it and has been rewarded with a wicket. A five-fer for him as well, his first in Test cricket. He has been exceptional thus far. This is full and angling in, from around off, Kyle Verreynne remains on the back foot and looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge shout for LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Matt Henry convinces Tom Latham to take the review by saying that it's full enough and height won't be a factor. No bat there on the UltraEdge. Ball Tracking shows three reds and another set batter goes!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Matt Henry

Commentary.Commentary: A short one to end the over, on middle. Marco ducks under it.
Full and wide outside off. Jansen offers no shot.
A short ball, on middle, Kyle Verreynne pulls it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Again this is outside off and Kyle shoulders arms to it.
Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, outside off. Kyle taps it to point.
On a length, on off. Jansen taps it on the surface.
Good stop! Around off, on a length. Jansen plays it back to the right of Henry and he puts a big dive to stop it.
Length and on middle. Jansen blocks it out.
BEATEN! A length ball, just around the off stump line. Jansen looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge and it flies over the stumps.
Short of a length, outside off, it shoots off the deck. Jansen has a feel for it and misses.
Full and angling on middle. Jansen defends off the front foot.
Fuller ball with some inward movement, on middle. Kyle Verreynne wrists it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Just short! A fuller ball, slanting outside of. Kyle Verreynne looks to push but gets an outside edge. The ball falls just short of the fielder at gully.
Fuller and outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, outside off. Kyle punches it nicely but the fielder at covers dives to stop the ball.
Short of a length, on middle. Blocked out on the leg side.
A full ball, outside off, away swing there. Kyle punches it to covers. Neil Wagner is down in his follow-through.
Very full and on middle. Jansen digs it out on the leg side.

Drinks break. Two wickets in the first hour after Lunch and the slide continues for South Africa. They tried to play some positive strokes but in the process have now lost both Temba Bavuma and Zubayr Hamza. The scoreboard is not reading even 100 and the Saffas are six down. Marco Jansen, the tall man, is the new batter.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Matt Henry gets his fourth wicket and another partnership is broken. Short of a length, outside off, extra bounce and some outward movement as well. Hamza has an unnecessary poke at it from the back foot. He gets an outside edge to the keeper, Tom Blundell judges the catch perfectly to his right. End of a fighting knock from Zubayr Hamza.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Blundell b Matt Henry

Commentary.Commentary: A length ball, drifting down the leg side. Hamza lets it through.
Around off, pushed to covers.
A length ball, outside off. Hamza shoulders arms to it. Tom Blundell fumbles to collect it and Kyle Verreynne is halfway mark to take a quick bye but is sent back in time.
Length ball, on middle. Hamza blocks it out.
Length ball, on the pads. Hamza tucks it to mid-wicket for a quick single to end the over.
Another short one, on middle. Hamza sits under it.
Bangs a short one now, around off. Hamza sways away from the line of the ball.
Short of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne hops and pushes it to the left of covers for a single.
A length ball, outside off, was the slower one this time. Kyle is early as he punches it to mid off.
Length ball, angling across, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, at 140 clicks, on middle. Hamza blocks it on the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Kyle pushes it through covers for a single.
Length and on off. Kept out.
Fuller and outside off. Kyle looks to push away from the body but gets an inside edge to the leg side.
Length ball, outside off. Kyle defends with an angled bat to gully.
FOUR! Edged! A length ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne looks to punch with soft hands but it takes the outside edge through gully for a boundary.
Keeps it on a length around off, angling away, Zubayr Hamza covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
In the channel outside off, Zubayr Hamza has nothing to do with it.
Outside off, that is left alone for the keeper to collect.
A touch short again, on off, Kyle punches it through covers for a single.
Back of a length, around off, Kyle defends it from the back foot.
Around leg, on a length, defended on the leg side.
Change from both ends then as Neil Wagner (4-2-3-0) is back on.

DROPPED! Fuller in length around off, angling in at 137.7 kph, Zubayr Hamza drives it with the full face of his bat but fails to keep it down. Matt Henry sticks his right hand out but fails to grab it. A life for Hamza.
A length ball on off, Zubayr Hamza stays on the back foot and offers a straight blade in defense.
Short and around off, Kyle pulls it down to fine leg for a single.
On a length and around off, defended from the back foot to point.
Around off, on a length, blocked to the off side.
Fuller and around off, at 132 clicks, Kyle Verreynne tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Change. Matt Henry (9-4-16-3) is back into the attack.
On the pads, tucked behind square leg for one.

False shot! Kyle Jamieson is mixing up his variations well. Delivers an outswinger around off, fuller in length, Kyle Verreynne gets a soft leading edge as he attempts to flick. The ball rolls way to covers.
Back of a length, on off, it's defended from the back foot to covers.
Inswinger, on the shorter side around off, Verreynne defends it from the back foot to point.
Goes fuller and on off, this has been pushed off the front foot to covers.
FOUR! Slapped! Kyle Jamieson delivers it short and wide outside off, Kyle Verreynne rises on his back foot and slaps it through backward point for a boundary.
Sliding down the leg side, Zubayr Hamza tries to buy some cheap runs with a gentle flick but misses.
There's the inswinger, around off, Kyle Verreynne plays very late and pushes it with an angled bat through point for a single.
Goes wide of the crease but serves it also wide outside off, a comfortable leave for Kyle Verreynne.
Shortish and on off, Kyle plays from the back foot to gully.
On a length around middle, Kyle Verreynne brings a straight bat down as he defends it towards mid on.
Fuller in length and outside off, Zubayr Hamza reaches out and drives it from the bottom part of his bat through covers. Three runs taken.
A length ball on off, defended from the back foot safely.
Well bowled! There is still enough in this pitch. Kyle Jamieson serves it close to off and gets it to hold its line, Kyle Verreynne pushes inside the line as he tries to defend and gets beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
Delivers it on a good length around off, at 133.1 kph, Kyle Verreynne is on his toes in defense.
On a length and around off, Kyle Verreynne defends it from the back foot to point.
Drifting down the leg side, Zubayr Hamza is unable to flick and it goes off his pads to fine leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Stays back inside the crease, uses the angle of the bowler and nudges it in front of square leg for a single.
Outswinger to follow the inswinger, outside off, Zubayr Hamza allows it through to the keeper.
This one lands on a length around off and jags back in sharply with extra bounce. Zubayr Hamza fails to defend and is hit on the thigh pad.
A bumper around middle, Zubayr Hamza sits underneath it.
Full and on middle, pushed down the ground again, this time to mid on. Not in the gap.

FOUR! That's a lovely shot. Fullish and around off, angling in and then moving away a touch, Zubayr Hamza leans forward, doesn't try to hit it hard and just caresses it past the diving short extra cover fielder for a boundary.
On a length and outside off, holding its line, Kyle Verreynne shoulders arms. Maiden.
Fullish and around off, angling in, Kyle plays late and pushes it to the right of mid on.
Harmless delivery, wide outside off, it's left alone.
Jamieson goes fuller and angles it in around off, Kyle Verreynne flicks but finds the square leg fielder.
Back of a length, around off and shaping in, Kyle Verreynne goes on his back foot and defends it towards mid on.
Inswinger from Jamieson but the line is quite wide outside off, an easy leave for Kyle Verreynne.
Too full and around off at 131.5 kph, Hamza drives it down the ground off the inner half and finds mid on.
Bouncer around off, at 125.1 kph, Zubayr Hamza leans back and allows it through to the keeper.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it towards mid off.

FOUR! Nice shot! Southee digs it in short around off at 133.3 kph, Zubayr Hamza swivels on the back foot and pulls it through square leg for a boundary. He has tried to stay positive since the Lunch break.
Southee goes wide of the crease and darts in a length ball around off, Zubayr Hamza defends it from the back foot.
Bowls it on a length and close to off, Zubayr Hamza plays close to his body and defends it on the leg side.
Shortish and on off, Hamza hangs on the back foot and forces it towards covers for a single.
Back of a length, around off, Zubayr Hamza is on the back foot in defense.
Lands it on a length around off, shaping in, Hamza is on the back foot as he defends it down on the surface.
Slanting down the leg side, Verreynne clips it fine down the leg side for a single.
Around off, on a length, Kyle Verreynne defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Kyle Jamieson goes searching for a yorker around middle, it turns out to be a low full toss and Kyle Verreynne keeps it out safely on the leg side.
Pitches it up and around off, Hamza is forward as he pushes it defensively to covers.
Angling in from around off, again on a length, this time Zubayr Hamza defends it solidly off the front foot.
A length ball outside off, Zubayr Hamza allows it through.

Edgy! Southee dishes out a full ball outside off, Zubayr Hamza has a loose waft at it and edges it towards Henry Nicholls at gully. It dies in front of him and sneaks behind. The batters cross for a couple of runs.
Southee tries to repeat the last delivery albeit, from the leg stump line, Kyle Verreynne tucks it off his pads to square leg and opens his account with a single.
Serves it on a length and outside off, shaping away, Kyle Verreynne allows it through to the keeper.
On a length again, outside off, shoots off the deck. Hamza, on his toes, drops it to point.
On a length, on off, Hamza stays back and defends it to point.
Length ball, wide outside off. Left alone.
Length and on middle, Hamza hops and gets behind the line of the ball to defend it.
Fuller and on off. Hamza blocks off the front foot.
On a length, around off. Hamza blocks it out.
Kyle Verreynne is the new batter with South Africa staring down the barrel. Also, it's going to be Kyle Jamieson (6-1-13-1) to operate from the opposite end.

OUT! TAKEN! Just when you thought that South Africa are off to a good start, they give away a wicket. Very soft dismissal, this! It was a good over for the Proteas until this ball. A full ball, slanting on the pads. Temba Bavuma flicks it uppishly to short mid-wicket where Devon Conway takes a sharp catch to his right. Half the side down now for the Proteas.
Commentary.Howout: c Devon Conway b Tim Southee

Commentary.Commentary: Full and outside off, pushed through covers for a couple of runs.
Fuller again, on middle, tucked to mid-wicket for one more. 50 up for South Africa.
FOUR! A positive start by Hamza! This is full and on middle. Hamza pushes it gently, past the bowler and wide of mid on for a boundary.
South Africa are underway in this session. On a length, angling on the pads, it is flicked to deep backward square leg for a single.
A full ball, on off, pushed to mid on.

Welcome back, folks! We're getting ready for the second segment of the day's play. The clouds have disappeared completely now and the Hagley Oval is bathed in bright sunshine. The pitch could have settled down a bit also. A quick huddle for the Kiwis before they get back on the field. Temba Bavuma and Zubayr Hamza have a big task in front of them as they walk out. Tim Southee to begin the second session as well...
... DAY 1, SESSION 2 ...

South Africa have their backs to the wall after a sorry start. Temba Bavuma and Zubayr Hamza have spent some time in the middle and despite getting beaten on plenty of occasions, they have braved the conditions. The touring team would be hoping for a partnership between them when the action resumes after Lunch. Do join us at 6.10 am IST (12.40 am GMT) for the second session.

A morning of dominance for the Black Caps. Everything has gone according to the plan. Tom Latham opted to bowl and his bowlers vindicated his decision. Matt Henry impressed the most with his pace and the ability to move the ball both ways. He picked up the first wicket by dismissing Dean Elgar cheaply and then hunted down two wickets in one over after returning for his second spell. The rest of the Kiwi bowlers were also right on the money and tested the South African batters with some impeccable lines and lengths.
Left alone! This is full and slanting outside off. Hamza with an easy leave. That will be Lunch on Day 1.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Hamza offers no shot. Last ball before the Lunch break coming up...
A sharp bouncer now, around off. Hamza evades it.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Pitches it up, outside off. Hamza keeps his cool as he leaves it alone. Driving length but Hamza is not tempted.
Short ball but down the leg side. Hamza ducks under it.
New Zealand can squeeze in one more over before Lunch.
A length ball, on middle. Bavuma turns it to short mid-wicket.
Angles it on the pads. Hamza flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
A length ball, around off. Hamza taps it on the off side.
On a length, on middle. Hamza defends it solidly.
On middle, pushed to short mid-wicket.
This is way down the leg side, on a length. Hamza misses his flick.

Finally some runs for South Africa after a long time! A full ball, outside off, Bavuma drives it to the left of cover where a misfield allows a couple of runs. First runs for South Africa after 28 balls.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Now induces an outside edge there as Temba tries to defend this length ball, but the ball falls well short of the fielder at third slip.
JAFFA! A length ball, outside off, it jags back in. Bavuma tries to defend with an angled bat but gets beaten on the outside edge. This is exceptional bowling from Wagner.
Very full this time, outside off, Bavuma misses his drive. He is getting fidgety just before Lunch.
BEATEN! A full ball, angling away outside off, Temba Bavuma had enough of defensive shots as he goes for the drive. He misses though.
Maiden to start for Colin de Grandhomme! A length ball, outside off. Left alone. Maiden.
Fuller and on off. Hamza plays it back to the bowler.
Colin de Grandhomme continues to bowl outside off, this one swings away but nothing for Hamza to play.
Length ball, outside off. Hamza is happy not to play that.
Outside off again, on a length, again some late shape there. Left alone.
A length ball, outside off, gets to shape away. Hamza lets it through.
Colin de Grandhomme to have a go with the ball. He can be counted as the slower version of Matt Henry, equally equipped to swing the ball both ways.
Fuller ball, outside off, it nips back in. Bavuma looks to defend off the front foot but hits off the inner half of the bat, back to the bowler.
This is outside off and Bavuma offers no shot to it.
Colin de Grandhomme is warming up...
Full ball, drifting outside off. Temba with yet another leave.
This is angled way outside off. Left alone.
Fuller and outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone.
A full ball, swinging in from around off. Bavuma gets on the front foot to defend but manages only an inside edge onto the pads.
Touch fuller, around off. Zubayr keeps it out on the off side.
Now targets the stumps but Hamza gets his bat down to defend it.
Outside off, on a length. Hamza watches it all the way to the keeper.
Length ball, outside off, it swings away and shoots off the deck as well. Left alone. Good take by the keeper.
On middle. Blocked out.
Sharp leave! On a length and nipping back in, just around off. Hamza shoulders arms to it and the ball whizzes past the off stump.
Length ball, outside off, left alone.
Touch fuller, on middle. Temba dead-bats it.
Wagner tries the away-swinger this time but bowls it way outside off. Easy leave for Bavuma.
Length ball, swinging in, on middle, Bavuma gets behind the trajectory of the ball and blocks it on the leg side.
A full ball, slanting outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, onto the pads. Hamza clips it to fine leg for a single.
Neil Wagner is inserted into the attack.
A length ball, extra pace and on off. Bavuma defends it away from the body, on the surface.
A length ball, straight on middle. Hamza, on the back foot, tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
On middle, on a length. Hamza defends it solidly.
An appeal but there was an inside edge! A full ball, angling around middle and leg. Hamza looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On a length, outside off. Hamza defends with soft hands to the slip cordon.
A length ball, outside off, shaping away. Hamza shoulders arms to it.
Fractionally short and on off, Temba is on his toes as he plays it defensively to short leg.
Back of a length, outside off, Temba Bavuma shoulders arms.
Outside off, left alone.

Ooohhh...almost drags it on. A nice piece of bowling first up to the new batsman. Kyle Jamieson dishes out an inswinger, around off and nipping in, Zubayr Hamza tries to defend but it takes the inner edge and goes through his legs to fine leg. A single is taken.
Full and on middle, it's clipped through square leg for a single.
Outside off, Temba offers no shot.
Zubayr Hamza walks out to the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT! Matt Henry has two in the over, what an attempt from the speedster! He is getting the ball to talk both ways and looking very lethal. This time he delivers a length ball close to off at 141.5 kph and gets it to move away late. Rassie van der Dussen doesn't do a lot wrong there as he is on the back foot, trying to defend the trajectory of the ball. But the away movement results in a thick outside edge and Tim Southee takes another sharp catch at third slip. New Zealand have four wickets in the morning session thus far and are roaring. Also, a word of praise for Tom Latham who brought on Matt Henry for his second spell and he has done the trick.
Commentary.Howout: c Tim Southee b Matt Henry

Commentary.Commentary: Slightly short and on off, Temba goes back and taps it down to covers for a quick run. He opens his account.
Beaten! Close to off and on a length, Bavuma pushes inside the line and misses.
On a length and outside off, Temba allows it through to the keeper.
Temba Bavuma is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Matt Henry cooks up a spicy delivery. He hurls it around off on the shorter side at 133 kph and gets it to shoot up off the surface. Aiden Markram goes on his toes as he attempts to punch it through the line. He fails to middle his shot and it goes closely past the outside edge to the keeper. There is some sound and Tom Blundell secures the catch behind the stumps. They are celebrating but Aiden Markram is looking unsure. He feels that he has not edged it and goes for the referral. A big spike on the UltraEdge. Aiden will have to go and he takes one review along with him.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Blundell b Matt Henry

Commentary.Commentary: Review! Aiden Markram takes the review after being given caught behind. UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball passes the bat. Review lost and Aiden Markram has to walk back.
Beave leave. On a good length around off, shaping back in, Aiden shoulders arms and it goes over the stumps.

FOUR! Good shot! Kyle Jamieson alters his length to go short and delivers it around off, Rassie van der Dussen stands tall inside the crease and pulls it delightfully behind square leg for a boundary.
Inswinger this time around off, Rassie van der Dussen closes the face of his bat and helps it to the right of mid-wicket.
Fuller in length and on middle, Rassie van der Dussen flicks it across the line but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
A harmless delivery outside off, an easy leave for Rassie van der Dussen.
Superb delivery to beat the edge. Full and close to off, angling in and shaping away with extra bounce, Rassie van der Dussen tries to defend but it whistles past his bat.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Beaten! Full and around off, Markram is beaten as he gets on the front foot to defend.
FOUR! Edgy! Width there outside off, Aiden Markram runs out of patience and throws his bat at it. It takes a thick outside edge and races past the diving gully fielder for a boundary.
Another delivery in the channel outside off, again Aiden makes a leave.
Outside off, left alone.
Review time! Matt Henry convinces Tom Latham enough to take the LBW appeal upstairs. No question of the bat there. Ball Tracking shows it to be the umpire's call on hitting the wickets.

NOT OUT! Huge shout for an lbw, the finger stays down again. There is some discussion in the slip cordon about the height. Mixed reaction and Latham hesitantly takes the DRS. Coming to the delivery, it's served on a length around off, shaping back in off the seam, Markram offers no shot and is pinged on the pads. They appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The Ball Tracking shows that it would have brushed the bails. Umpire's call.
Fuller in length, around off at 140.4 kph, Rassie van der Dussen plays a punchy drive through covers and takes a single.
Fullish and outside off, holding its line, Aiden covers his stumps and leaves it alone. Quality over.
Kyle Jamieson goes wide of the crease and angles in a shortish ball around off, Rassie van der Dussen gets across and tucks it off his hips to long leg for one.
In the corridor outside off, Rassie shoulders arms.
A length ball outside off, played down with soft hands to point.
Around off, defended on the off side.
Appeal for an lbw! A touch short in length, around off and shaping back in, Rassie van der Dussen offers no shot and is hit high on the front leg. They appeal but the umpire remains unmoved.
Angling down the leg side, Rassie van der Dussen fails to work it away and it goes off his pads to the on side. They cross for a leg bye.
Awkward bounce. Matt Henry delivers it short and around off, Rassie van der Dussen goes on his toes and keeps it out from the inner portion of his bat to square leg.
Presses forward to a full ball and pushes it through the line. Finds the cover fielder.

Shout for an lbw, not given. Henry lands it on a length around off and gets it to shape back in, Rassie van der Dussen is forward in defense but misses. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal but to no avail. Missing leg, shows the replay.
In the channel outside off, it's left alone.
Serves it on a length around middle, Rassie van der Dussen defends it on the leg side.

Drinks! New Zealand dominated the first hour as they got both the openers fairly early. They have kept things tight and will hope the same in the next hour. Aiden Markram is looking solid despite getting beaten on a few occasions while Rassie van der Dussen is making himself comfortable. South Africa need the current pair to build a partnership now. Also, Matt Henry (4-2-9-1) is back into the attack.
A beautiful outswinger, outside off at 126.7 kph, Aiden Markram withdraws his bat at the last moment. Maiden.
Fractionally short and outside off, Aiden Markram looks to push at it again and gets beaten.
Beaten all ends up! This one is a cross-seamer. Kyle Jamieson pitches it up and around off, getting it to straighten, Aiden Markram pushes inside the line and misses.
Action replay of the previous delivery. Markram is quite content with his leaving game at the moment.
In the zone outside off, on a good length again, Aiden Markram shoulders arms.
Beaten! Kyle Jamieson lands it on a good length, close to off, Aiden Markram hangs his bat out tamely in his attempt to defend and gets beaten.
Fullish and around off, Aiden Markram dabs it with gentle hands to point and keeps strike with a single.
Fractionally short and around leg, Rassie van der Dussen fails to work it away and it goes off the pads to fine leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Serves it full and on off, forcing the batsman to play at it. Rassie van der Dussen is forward as he allows the ball to come at him and then he dead-bats it on the off side.
Southee gets closer to the off stump line with his outswinger but it's not close enough to trouble the batter. Left alone.
Another outswinger, full and wide outside off, van der Dussen is not chasing it.
On a length and outside off, an outswinger, Rassie van der Dussen makes a leave.
In the channel outside off, quite wide, an easy leave for Aiden.

Unplayable again. Kyle Jamieson this time. He lets it out on a length around off, at 130 clicks and the ball moves away late. Aiden Markram is inside the crease in his attempt to block but it beats the outside edge.
A tempter from Kyle Jamieson. He serves it on a driving length outside off, Aiden Markram shows restrain as he allows it through.
Back of a length, outside off, Rassie goes on the back foot and taps it down in front of square on the off side. They cross for a single.
Hurls across a length delivery, in the channel outside off, Rassie van der Dussen covers the stumps and allows it through.
Very full and around off, Rassie van der Dussen defends it back with an unstable front foot movement.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it safely. End of a probing over from Southee.
Unplayable! This is a gem from Southee. Perfect seam presentation, as it lands on a fuller length around off, Markram tries to play the line but it nips away a shade to beat the outside edge.
Play and a miss! Markram loses his patience and goes after it. Southee serves it from wide of the crease, it's short and wide outside off, Aiden tries to cut but it beats his bat.
Puts it on a fuller length, close to off at 128.4 kph, Aiden Markram feels like driving it but it takes the inside edge, pings him on the pads and rolls tamely to covers.
Delivers it on a length and in the zone outside off, shaping away, Aiden presses forward to cover the line and shoulders arms.
Around off, on a length, Aiden Markram defends it from the back foot to covers.
A length ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen is in two minds as he tries to leave it but keeps his bat hanging out. Gets a bottom edge to the slip cordon and it goes on one bounce.
Pitches it up, outside off. Markram drops it to cover-point for another single.
Full ball, around off. Rassie van der Dussen is off the mark as he pushes it to the left of mid off for a single.
Rassie van der Dussen is the number 4 batter.

OUT! TAKEN! Kyle Jamieson gets the wicket in his first over and the debutant's stay at the crease is over! Kyle delivers it on a length, around off and there is some extra pace and bounce as well. Sarel Erwee is squared up as he looks to defend but only manages to get an outside edge to first slip where Daryl Mitchell takes the catch nicely.
Commentary.Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary.Commentary: Full again, on middle, Markram flicks it through square leg and three runs are taken before the fine leg fielder gets across to stop it.
Full ball, outside off. Aiden Markram blocks it out.
Here comes the first bowling change. Kyle Jamieson replaces Matt Henry from this end.

NOT OUT! Southee makes this one to come back in. It lands on a length and is around off. Sarel covers his off stump and shoulders arms to it but gets hit on the back leg. A huge, huge appeal for LBW but not given. We can hear the Kiwis saying height is not the issue and they take the review. No bat there. Ball Tracking shows that the impact is with the umpire's call and it's also missing the stumps.

Huge shout for an lbw! Tim Southee is almost running in celebration as he turns to appeal. The umpire shakes his head. Someone from the slip cordon suggests that - 'It's definitely not high!' Tom Latham has a word with Southee and takes the UDRS. The Ball Tracking shows that the impact is with the umpire's call. Unlucky, Tim.
Fullish delivery, around off, driven to covers.
On a length, on middle, Erwee gets behind the line of the ball as he blocks this one.
Length ball, outside off. Sarel hops and taps it back to Southee.
Angles across a length ball, outside off. Sarel covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
Fuller ball, angling outside off. Erwee shoulders arms to it.
This is way outside off, on a length. Aiden Markram leaves it alone with ease.
Back of a length, on off and jags back in as well. Aiden Markram stays back to defend but it takes the inside edge and he gets hit on the thigh pad.
Fuller now, on middle, it is flicked to mid-wicket.
Short of a length and on middle. Markram nudges it to square leg.

FOUR! Edged but through the gap! A length ball, outside off. Aiden Markram looks to defend off the front foot but it takes the outer half of the blade and beats the diving gully fielder for a boundary.
A full ball, nipping back in, on middle. Aiden wrists it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off. Erwee defends on the front foot.
Southee comes around the wicket and serves it on a length and outside off, it swings away late. Sarel makes a good leave.
Fuller and outside off. Erwee lunges and leaves it alone.
Around off, on a length. Blocked out.
FOUR! First boundary of the innings! Short of a length, on middle. Sarel Erwee shuffles across and pulls it to the fine leg fence.
Kyle Jamieson is warming up...
A length ball, around off. Sarel prods to defends it towards mid off.
Short of a length, on off. Markram watchfully blocks it.
Three taken! A full ball, way outside off. Sarel drives it nicely through covers for three runs.
Outside off again and Erwee is happy to let it through.
Length ball, angling outside off. Left alone.
Ohhh! That seamed back in sharply! On a length, around off, it lands and shapes back in and hits Sarel Erwee on the back pad who shoulders arms to it. The appeal is made but it's too high.
Sarel Erwee with a positive shot! Henry pitches it up, outside off. Sarel punches it with the full face of the bat, wide of mid off and two runs are taken before the fielder cuts it off.
A length ball, outside off. Aiden lets it through.
A length ball, just outside off. Aiden Markram watches all the way as he shoulders arms to it.
Aiden Markram is off the mark here! Southee goes wide of the crease and angles it full and on middle. Markram flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
On middle, on a fuller length and Markram leans to defend it out.
On a length, around middle. Blocked out solidly.

An appeal for LBW but turned down! A length ball, angling around middle and leg. Aiden Markram looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but Southee later gestures that height might be the issue. To us, it looked like going down the leg side.
Tight leave by Sarel! This is on a length and in the corridor, around off. Sarel plants his front foot forward and shoulders arms to it.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Sharp bounce there! On a length, just outside off. Sarel stands tall and lets it through to the keeper.
Length and on middle, Sarel rocks back and defends it to square leg.
This one nips away, fuller and outside off. Sarel leaves it alone.
Half-volley by Henry, outside off. Erwee prods to drive but it goes off the inner half of the blade, back towards the bowler.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Sarel Erwee is underway in Test cricket! This is full and on the pads, it is flicked to deep backward square leg for a single.
Length ball, angling outside off. Erwee offers no shot.
Length ball, swinging away late but down the leg side. Erwee misses his flick.
Outside off again, on a length. Sarel shoulders arms to it.
Tad fuller, way outside off. Easy leave for Erwee.
On a length, on middle. Aiden defends it out. Successful start for Matt Henry as he opens with a wicket maiden.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Aiden Markram is the number 3 batter.

OUT! TAKEN! Superb catch by Tim Southee and New Zealand get the opposition skipper. The first two deliveries were almost on a length and this time Henry serves it a touch fuller, slanting around off at 136.4 kph. It nips away a shade as well after landing. Dean Elgar is drawn forward to drive but it takes the outside edge to third slip where Tim Southee goes down low to his left to take a sharp catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Tim Southee b Matt Henry

Commentary.Commentary: Angles it across, outside off, on a length. It's left alone.
A length ball, outside off. Elgar shoulders arms to it.
Almost a yorker to start with from Henry, around off. Elgar gets his bat down to defend it.
Matt Henry to share the new ball from the opposite end. Three slips and a gully for him as well.
Full ball from over the wicket, on the pads. Sarel Erwee gets squared up slightly as he tries to work it away. Misses and it goes off his pads to short leg.
South Africa and Dean Elgar are underway! Fuller ball, outside off. Elgar punches with soft hands through cover-point for a single.
Touch fuller from Southee, on off and Elgar, on the front foot, defends it out.
A length ball, slanting around off. Dean prods to block it on the leg side.
Short leg comes into play. Will Young is under the lid.
Length ball, on off, Elgar gets on the front foot as he blocks it out.
Swing straightaway! On a length, swinging way down the leg side. Elgar shuffles in his crease and misses his flick. Good collecttion from the keeper.

All in readiness. A quick huddle from New Zealand before they spread on the field. We can see some blue skies at the moment. The pitch is green in colour, so it's going to be a big challenge for the openers of South Africa. Dean Elgar and the debutant Sarel Erwee walk out now. Tim Southee to kick off proceedings with the new cherry. Three slips and a gully in place. Both teams take the customary knee in support of the Black Lives Matter movement. Here we go...

The sun is peeping out a bit from the clouds as the players walk out. Both teams line up in the middle for their respective national anthem. South Africa's first, followed by New Zealand's. We're minutes away from the first ball.
New Zealand (Playing XI) - Tom Latham (C), Will Young, Devon Conway, Henry Nicholls, Daryl Mitchell, Tom Blundell (WK), Colin de Grandhomme, Kyle Jamieson, Tim Southee, Neil Wagner, Matt Henry.

South Africa (Playing XI) - Dean Elgar (C), Sarel Erwee (On Debut), Aiden Markram, Rassie van der Dussen, Temba Bavuma, Zubayr Hamza, Kyle Verreynne (WK), Marco Jansen, Kagiso Rabada, Glenton Stuurman (On Debut), Duanne Olivier.
TOSS - Up goes the coin and it lands in favour of Tom Latham. New Zealand will BOWL first!

New Zealand's coach Gary Stead confirmed that Matt Henry will replace Boult which seems the home side will go with an all-pace attack while Dean Elgar has hinted that Sarel Erwee might get an opportunity to make his Test debut. Will he get the nod? Only time will tell. Toss and team news coming up shortly...

New Zealand will be without some veteran players like Kane Williamson and Trent Boult. With Ross Taylor now retired, they need someone like him to fill his void. They drew their last home series against Bangladesh while South Africa won 2-1 against India. The Kiwis will enjoy the home condition but with a few senior players missing, they have to get their best game against a side that is sitting fourth on the World Test Championship table.

Good morning, everyone! There is a special feeling when New Zealand host a Test series. Such is the charm of this place. The lush green outfield and strong winds are the hallmarks here and they bring a different kind of challenge for the touring teams. South Africa are in the country to challenge the supremacy of the Black Caps at home and the coming two Test matches are going to be full of excitement. We are here for the first one in Christchurch, the second one is also here, and can't wait to get going. Stay tuned for more...
... FIRST TEST ...
The players are back on the field. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee are the openers for South Africa with just one aim at the moment - survive the day's play. Tim Southee to speed in...
... THIRD INNINGS ...

It was a dismal bowling show by the touring team. They were inconsistent with their lines and suffered. To add to their misery, as many as seven catches went down and they were made to pay heavily. The final wicket stand between Tom Blundell and Matt Henry summed up South Africa's performance, the last pair added 94 runs and stretched the lead for New Zealand near 400. The Proteas now will have to bat out of their skin to come out of this Test match unscathed. 9 overs in the day's play left. Let's see what happens next...

A strong batting show by the Kiwis and they were nicely assisted by some below-par bowling and mediocre catching from South Africa. One Henry did the damage with the ball, the other Henry took the charge with the bat. Henry Nicholls, who was dropped twice, went on to score a superb century and his stand with Devon Conway handed the home team the platform. This morning, Neil Wagner went hammer and tongs to deflate South Africa's confidence. The rate with which New Zealand batted on Day 2 was exceptional and that has handed them a good advantage.

The best stand of the Kiwi innings which came for the final wicket has been broken finally and South Africa would be feeling relieved. Two days of toil for them and they are way behind in this Test match, trailing by 387 runs.

OUT! CAUGHT! Heartbreak for Tom Blundell. Beauty of a delivery! Jansen serves it on a good length around off and takes it away with the angle. Tom Blundell hangs on the back foot and feels for it inside the line. It goes very closely past the outside edge and the keeper appeals after collecting the ball. The finger stays down and Elgar gets convinced to take the DRS. There is a spike on the UltraEdge and New Zealand are all out for 482.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Too full and around off, Matt drives it through covers for a single.
On a driving length outside off, Henry shows restrain as he lets it be. At the moment, he seems to be batting for Blundell who is 4 shy of a hundred.
Angling away from the batter, on a good length, Henry plays inside the line and misses.
Leading edge but safe! Full and around leg, Henry tries to flick but closes the face of his bat early. It pops out but drops safely on the off side.
Fuller in length and outside off, Henry drives it in the gap at extra cover and takes a single.
Hurls a length ball in the channel outside off, it lands and straightens, Henry allows it through to the keeper.
Full and around off, Henry keeps his weight on the back foot and pushes it to wide mid off.
Shortish and close to off, Blundell jumps on the back foot and pushes it gently towards mid off. Calls for two but will get only a run. Nervous 90s.
Back of a length, around off, Matt pushes it from the back foot to covers for a single.
FOUR! Nice shot! Short in length and wide outside off, Henry reaches out for it and flat-bats it over backward point for a boundary. The way he is batting, a century seems to be loading for him.
Change in bowling. Kagiso Rabada is back for another burst.
Back of a length, around off and angling away, Blundell goes back inside the crease and tries to whip it on the leg side but misses.
Short and on middle, Tom Blundell pulls it over square leg and collects a couple. Moves to 95.
Taps a length ball to cover-point and rushes to the other end for a run.
Stays back and pushes it through the line, finds the fielder at gully.
Around off, on a length, blocked.
Fuller and around off, driven down towards mid off for a run.
Marco Jansen is back on.
Full and outside off, Henry works it on the leg side but not in the gap.
Presses forward and defends a full delivery to the off side.
Goes on the back foot and forces it through mid off for one.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
FIFTY FOR HENRY! He is having a fantastic Test match. Loopy and around off, Matt is forward and strokes it towards mid off for a run. The local lad raises his bat and enjoys the ovation.
FOUR! Shot! Henry moves to 49! Loopy and full outside off, Matt Henry gets forward with a big stride and bludgeons it to the deep cover fence.
Another run! On off, this is guided down to third man for one.
Shorter and on the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, kept out again.
On the fuller side, Henry strokes it to mid off.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it on middle, defended.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Loopy and full around middle, Henry works it off his pads but finds square leg.
Flatter and shorter on off, Matt goes on the back foot and pushes it back to the bowler.
Beaten! Short and outside off, Henry gets back to cut but misses.
Loopy and full, around off, Henry draws forward in defense.
Walks forward and pushes a full ball in the gap at covers for one.
Fuller and on middle, eased down to long on for a run.

Drinks break. It has been a frustrating last hour for the Proteas. The record last-wicket stand has taken the lead over 350 now and Matt Henry, in particular, has punished their bowlers. South Africa are just going through the motions, waiting for this stand to end somehow.
This one is served on the pads, Matt has worked it behind square leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, forced down to long on for a single.
Short in length and angling down the leg side, Tom tries to work it away but misses.
Gets back and taps it down to covers. They cross for a run as the fielder scores a direct hit at the keeper's end. The ball deflects away and the batters collect two more.
Beaten! Full again from Glenton Stuurman, it's outside off Henry tries to drive but misses.
Full and wide outside off, driven to deep cover for a single.
A touch short and on middle, some extra bounce, Matt Henry goes back and defends.
Fuller and on off, Blundell uses his feet and knocks it down to long on for a single.
Drags his length short and delivers it on off, Tom goes back and works it to mid-wicket.
Presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Flatter and on off, defended off the back foot.

FOUR! Boom! Aiden Markram has been brought back into the attack and he has been greeted with a boundary. Tom Blundell uses his feet to dance down the track and clobbers it behind the bowler's head for a boundary.
Review time!

NOT OUT! It is clipping the bails! Not a bad review to be honest! This is on a length and around middle, it jags back in. Henry hops and looks to defend. He misses and gets hit on the pads over the flap. An appeal but turned down. Elgar reviews but replays show that it is clipping the top of the leg pole. Umpire's call.
A yorker now on middle, Henry jams it out to mid on.
On the up! Length and on middle, this is driven back towards the bowler. Glenton Stuurman gets a hand to it so it is just a single as the ball rolls behind.
Finds the gap again! Not off the middle but hit well enough to get three! Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through mid-wicket. The fielder chases it down and keeps it down to three.
He really went hard at that! Shorter and outside off, Henry looks to pull but misses. He is oozing with confidence now.
FOUR! Crunched! Henry is dealing in boundaries here! That is whacked! Outside off, this is hit with disdain through covers. No chance for the fielder in the deep. The lead is now 350.
On off, this is defended.
Shorter and outside off, Tom Blundell plays it down to third man for a couple of runs.
Short and on the body, this is pulled down to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Up and over! Adding to the pain here! Henry lofts this full ball on off over the bowler's head for a boundary. The 50-run stand comes up and the lead is getting close to 350 now.
Good length and on middle, Henry blocks.
A short one, Henry evades it.
FOUR! That is as straight as they come! Fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell shows the maker's name and creams it past the bowler and down to the fence.
On middle, defended.
FOUR! This is put away! A little bit of width on offer outside off, the length is also shortish. It is cut through point for a boundary.
On the bounce! Outside off, Henry goes after it, it flies off the outer half towards deep point and lands in front of the fielder. A single is taken.
On the stumps, blocked.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Change! Glenton Stuurman is on!
Goes full and that too is negotiated well as it is played to mid on.
FOUR! The short ball is just not working against Henry! Not sure why they are continuing with this ploy. This is outside off, Henry hops and whacks it over covers for a boundary.
On middle, blocked.
Slips this one down the leg side, Henry looks to flick but misses.
On off and on a length. This is pushed to covers.
A short one, it is evaded.
FOUR! Sheer timing! Just uses the pace of the bowler and finds the gap! On the pads, Tom Blundell stays back and works it through square leg. Frustrating for the visitors and good for the hosts.
Again! Short one, Blundell easily rocks back and pulls it through mid-wicket and takes two. He has looked unfazed against that short one.
A full toss, Tom Blundell fails to take toll of it as he is taken by surprise, he plays it to mid on.
Leading edge but it goes over! Just nothing going South Africa's way! On middle, Henry looks to flick, against the angle, it goes off the leading edge over Bavuma at covers for one.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Another good pull shot! He rides the bounce and pulls it all along the ground through square leg for one.
Angled into the pads this time, Henry looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Yet again looks to ramp this delivery over the slip cordon but misses. Not a bad idea as there is no one at third man so if he connects, it is a certain boundary.
Shortish and on off, Henry looks to play the upper-cut but misses. He is looking to play all the shots. Quite confident at the moment and why not!
FOUR! Henry is adding to the misery! What a shot this is! A shot a top-order player would feel proud of! Shortish and on off, Henry stays back and caresses it past cover and mid off for a boundary.
Back of a length and on middle, defended.
Another single! All these runs will be frustrating for the Saffas. Shorter and on the body, this is pulled in front of square leg for one.

PUT DOWN! That though was a tough chance. A really good effort! Outside off and full. Matt Henry throws his bat at it, it goes off the outer half uppishly down towards deep backward point. Sarel Erwee runs to his left and dives, he gets one hand to it but it does not stay in. The batters take two.
This is really good batting from Henry! Finding the gaps well! Shorter and outside off, he guides it past backward point for a couple more.
Effort ball! Shorter and outside off, takes off after landing. Henry looks to cut but is beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, good length, defended.
FOUR! Cracked! Here comes 400 in style! Shorter and on off, Henry slaps it through cover-point and this races away to the fence.
Shorter and outside off, Tom cuts but finds point.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
This is right off the middle. Top shot! Back of a length and on off, Henry strokes it through covers off the back foot for three.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers.

FOUR! EDGED AND OVER! Lead now over 300! Shorter and outside off, Henry looks to play it off the back foot through the off side, it goes off the outside edge over the slip fielders and into the third man fence.
Takes one on the first ball! Shorter and on middle, this is worked around the corner.
Yet another play and a miss! Another one angling away from the off pole. Henry looks to drive but does not connect yet again.
BEATEN! The angle almost does the trick! Fuller and on off, slanting away. Henry looks to drive but is beaten.
Another one outside off, Henry goes after it but no connection.
On the shorter side and outside off, angling away. Henry looks to cut but misses.
Two to get off the mark for Henry! On the pads, this is worked through square leg for a couple.
A single! Shorter and on middle, this is nudged on the leg side for one.
Matt Henry walks out to bat!

OUT! TAKEN! This time the fielder hangs on. It is the debutant, Sarel Erwee! Rabada finally gets his man and flashes a smile. This is short and on middle, Tim Southee looks to pull, he tries to do so off the front foot but is beaten for pace. It goes off the top edge, up in the air towards covers, Sarel Erwee does not look comfortable under it but manages to hang on and then tumbles onto the ground. He sees the funny side of it as his teammates come to pat his back.
Commentary.Howout: c Sarel Erwee b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: DROPPED AGAIN! This time it is Rassie van der Dussen! Not as easy as the last one but you expect him to take it. Shorter and outside off, Southee slaps it uppishly towards cover. Rassie dives to his left but spills it.
FOUR! Put away! Shorter and outside off, this is cut through point for a boundary. The frustration continues for South Africa.
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.

DROPPED! That should have been taken! Duanne Olivier, the culprit. That sums up South Africa's Test so far. Shorter and on middle, Southee looks to pull, this goes off the splice. Duanne Olivier needlessly dives to his left from mid on and looks to take it with two hands but spills it. He could have just moved to his left and taken it.
That one held in the surface! Shorter and on off, Southee checks his shot, it goes uppishly but lands short of covers.
Shorter and on middle, Blundell pulls it towards deep square leg for one. Rabada has overstepped yet again.
The successful experiment is over. Kagiso Rabada replaces Aiden Markram from this end.
Pitches it up and around off, Tim Southee pushes it down to mid off.
Fuller and outside off, driven through covers for a single.

FOUR! Wow! That's a delightful shot. Jansen delivers it full and outside off, Blundell gets on top of the bounce, transfers his weight into the drive and creams it through covers for a gorgeous boundary.
On a length, around middle and off, Blundell defends it back from the crease.
Serves it fuller and outside off, Tom drives through the line, good timing but he finds the mid off fielder.
Back of a length, around off, Blundell defends it watchfully off the back foot.
Fuller on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Flatter and a touch short on off, Southee stays back to work it around but perhaps gets some inside edge onto the pads.
Very full and around off, it's darted in at 87.9 kph, Southee defends it to covers.
Advances down the track to a full ball and whips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Presses forward to a full ball and defends it to the off side.
Spinning down the leg side, Blundell moves back and flicks it behind square leg for a couple of runs.
On a good length around middle, defended from the back foot by Southee.
Slightly short and angling away from the batsman, Tim Southee allows it through.
Fuller and around off, Tom inside-edges his attempted drive and it rolls to the left of the keeper. They cross for a single.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Jansen goes short on this occasion, around middle, Blundell stands tall inside the crease and pulls it firmly down to fine leg. The fielder in the deep makes a complete mess and allows a boundary. Fifty comes up for Tom Blundell, a very responsible knock from the Kiwi wicketkeeper.
Play and a miss! Fuller in length and wide outside off, Blundell reaches out and attempts to drive but fails to connect.
On a good length around middle, angling away, Blundell stays on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Quicker one, short and on off, Southee goes on the back foot and punches it to covers.
Fuller and around leg, it's eased behind square leg for a single.
Flighted and on middle, flicked across the line but straight to mid-wicket.
Too full and on middle, Tom walks forward and keeps it out on the leg side.
Tim Southee is the new batter.

OUT! CAUGHT! Markram has two and the move to continue with him after the Tea break has worked. Floated and full, landing around off, Kyle Jamieson tries to pump it down the ground but only manages to slice it in the air towards wide mid off. Kagiso Rabada settles underneath it and takes an easy catch. New Zealand lead by 273 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Kagiso Rabada b Aiden Markram

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up, a touch short and around off, Blundell gets back and helps it to square leg for a single.
Fuller and around leg, Jamieson flicks it off his pads but finds the mid on fielder.
Switches to over the wicket and angles across a short ball around off, Kyle feels for it and gets beaten.
Back of a length, around off, Blundell uses the angle of the bowler and works it in front of square leg for one.
Well driven again. Jamieson is at ease on the front foot as he caresses a full ball to deep cover. This time Bavuma chases it down and they take three runs.
Angles it in, on a length around off, Jamieson defends it from the back foot.
FOUR! Fine shot! Full and wide outside off, Kyle Jamieson reaches out for it and crunches it through covers for a cracking boundary.
Flatter and quicker around leg, defended to square leg.
Turning back in from around middle, Kyle Jamieson goes back and tucks it through square leg for one.
Around middle, Kyle Jamieson flicks it with the spin to mid-wicket.
Tossed up and around middle, defended back again, to the bowler's right.
Gets forward to a full ball and defends it back.
Flatter and a touch shorter on middle, Blundell goes back and helps it through square leg for a single.
In the zone outside off, Kyle Jamieson has nothing to do with it.
Delivers it full and outside off, Tom Blundell drives it towards mid off where the fielder fumbles and allows a single.
Loose this time from Tom Blundell. He goes chasing after a short delivery outside of and misses.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Around off, on a length, this time Blundell gets behind the line and blocks it safely.
Jansen begins with a length delivery, in the channel outside off and getting it to angle in, Tom Blundell takes a positive stride forward to cover the line and then leaves it alone.

It is time for the final session of the day! 36 overs left so we are in for a long one. The Kiwi batters, Kyle Jamieson and Tom Blundell make their way out to the middle. Marco Jansen to begin for the visitors. Here we go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

New Zealand will now hope they continue the good work and Tom Blundell along with the lower order extends the lead close to 350, at least. South Africa, on the other hand, will hope they can make quick work of the lower order, for that though they will need to bowl well which they have not. Will the last session go their way? Do join us at 8.30 am IST (3 am GMT) to find out.

The Saffas began the session brilliantly by getting Daryl Mitchell but they could not capitalize on it. Then there was a partnership between Henry Nicholls and Tom Blundell with the former getting to his ton but he fell soon after that. Colin de Grandhomme then came out and counter-attacked. He along with Blundell added 76 runs in no time. Have to say that stand has probably taken the game away from South Africa. They did get Colin towards the end of this session but not before he had done his job.

Another session which belongs to the hosts, yes they might have lost the three wickets but the pace they are scoring at is giving them the advantage and also, with the lead now over 250, the game is just drifting away from the visitors and at a rapid pace.
Loopy delivery, full and around off, Kyle Jamieson is on the front foot in defense. That will be Tea on Day 2.
FOUR! Brave shot from Jamieson just before Tea. Floated delivery, landing full and around middle, Kyle gets forward with his big reach and smashes it over mid on for a boundary.
Presses forward to a full ball and blocks it back safely.
Tossed up, around middle and leg, Kyle Jamieson goes back and nudges it towards fine leg for a couple.
Fuller and on off, Jamieson drills his drive back and Markram does well to stop it in his follow-through.
Flighted and full around off, Kyle Jamieson strides forward and defends it to the off side.
Fullish and on middle, Blundell is on the front foot and pushes it down to wide mid on.
Marco Jansen runs in from 'round the wicket and delivers it on a good length around off, Tom defends it from the back foot.
Ouch! That has hurt! Back of a length, around middle, Blundell tries to pull but it stays a bit low and strikes him near the box. He goes down in pain and takes some time to gather his breath.
Lands it on a length around off, Tom Blundell defends it from the back foot.
On a length, around leg, Kyle Jamieson tucks it in front of square leg for a single.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Kyle Jamieson walks in next. Also, Marco Jansen returns into the attack.

OUT! Colin de Grandhomme holes out! This was the trap laid by Elgar as he played on the ego of the batter by bringing in Aiden Markram. Floated and full, landing around off, Colin de Grandhomme advances down the track and tries to clear long on. He fails to get the desired distance and it's an easy catch for Marco Jansen in the deep. End of a very good knock by Colin. The 76-run stand has been broken and New Zealand lead by 254 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Marco Jansen b Aiden Markram

Commentary.Commentary: Flighted and on middle, Colin de Grandhomme flicks but finds mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, forced back to the bowler.
Loopy and full around off, Tom Blundell runs down the track and knocks it down to long on for a run.
Flatter and very full on middle, Tom works it on the leg side but finds mid-wicket.
Full and flighted on off, Blundell is on the front foot in defense.
Time for some spin! Aiden Markram to roll his arm now. This could be very interesting, especially against Colin de Grandhomme.

A beauty to end! They have hit these lengths so rarely and whenever they have, the visitors have managed to cause problems. On off, length, it lands and moves away late. Colin de Grandhomme is beaten as he tries to defend.
Drop and run! On middle, shorter, this is played on the off side for one.
Colin moves onto 45 now! Follows the two boundaries with a single as he plays it late and through square leg.

FOUR! This is just way too easy! The bowler over-compensates this time. Bowls it full and on the pads, Colin de Grandhomme whips it through square leg and it races away. The lead has jumped over 250 now.

FOUR! That is hammered! Colin de Grandhomme has raced to 40. This is a half-volley but it still has to be put away. Colin does it in style as he smashes it through covers. This one races away to the fence.
On middle, this is played to the man at mid on.
A single to follow the boundary now! On the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket. The lead is now 243.

FOUR! That is a fortunate boundary! Length and on off, this lands and jags back in a long way. Colin de Grandhomme looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge over the leg pole and down to the fine leg fence.
Two is the call and two is what they get! On middle, this is worked through square leg for a couple.
Outside off, left alone.
Goes short, does not trouble Colin much who pulls it down to fine leg for one.
A short one but it was outside off, Blundell looks to pull but misses.
On middle, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
Two more! Outside off, Colin de Grandhomme guides it through point for a couple.
Outside off, Colin de Grandhomme guides it through point for two.
On the stumps, it is kept out off the front foot to mid off.
On middle, it is blocked.
Crisp but does not find the gap! Fuller and on off, this is driven but straight to mid off.
Outside off, Tom Blundell does not play at it.
Angled into the pads, Colin works it through square leg for one.
On middle, Colin de Grandhomme keeps it out.
Outside off and on a length, left alone.

Another top stroke! The second new ball is going for runs! Shorter and on off, Tom Blundell stands tall and pushes it through covers for three. The 50-run stand comes up and it has come at a good rate as well.
Yet another delivery outside off, Tom Blundell lets it be.
Two more! On the pads, this is worked fine towards fine leg for a couple.

Angled into the pads, this is nudged on the leg side for one. Just not bowling to his field is Glenton Stuurman. He had a man at mid-wicket on the ball before and he bowled it outside off. On this ball, he had a cover fielder but bowls it on the pads.
FOUR! That is a beautiful shot! Fuller and outside off, Tom Blundell leans into it and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Angled into the pads, Tom Blundell flicks it to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, blocked.
Length again, Tom Blundell gets right behind the line and defends.
On middle, Colin pushes it to mid on.
Shorter and on middle, this is pulled down towards deep square leg for another run.
Solid again! On off, Blundell blocks it right under his eyes.
Just outside off, it is not played at.
Good length and on middle, Colin works it through the leg side and takes one.
Good length and on off, defended.

FOUR LEG BYES! Does not end it well too! On the pads, Tom Blundell looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and goes to the fine leg fence. Runs once again continue to flow. 15 from it and the lead is 218 runs.
Yet another one on the pads, Colin de Grandhomme flicks it through to fine leg for one more. This is not a good over from Glenton Stuurman so far.
FOUR MORE! This is a gift! On the pads, Colin de Grandhomme says thank you very much and whips it through square leg for a boundary.
That too could have ended over the ropes! Down the leg side, Colin swings but misses.
SIX! All the way! That is trademark Colin de Grandhomme! This is short and on the body, Colin de Grandhomme with one leg up, pulls it up and over the fine leg fence for a biggie.
Change! Glenton Stuurman is on now!
Down the leg side to begin with! Left alone.
Another one on the stumps, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, defended.
A huge appeal but turned down! This one swings in nicely from outside off, Tom looks to flick but misses and gets hit high on the pads. An appeal but turned down. Too high.
On the pads, this is flicked through mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Runs flowing here! Third boundary in the last 5 balls. This is hit on the up. On off, this is forced down the ground through mid off for a boundary. The lead crosses 200 now!
FOUR! Nice and fine! Second boundary in the over! On the pads, Tom Blundell works it fine and this one races away to the fence at fine leg.
On middle, Tom Blundell works it to mid-wicket.
Solid! Very solid! Good length and on off, Tom Blundell plays it right under his eyes and keeps it out.

FOUR! That is a lovely stroke! It made a cracking sound off the bat. This is the thing about the new ball, it just races off the bat. Fuller and on off, Tom shows the full face of the bat and strokes it past mid off for a boundary.
Shorter in length and angling into the middle pole line, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Goes fuller, gets it to shape back in just a little. This is jammed out to mid off.
End of a good over by Rabada! A testing one! On middle, Colin de Grandhomme keeps it out.
Just outside off, Colin de Grandhomme shuffles across and leaves it alone.
Extra bounce there! Back of a length and on off, takes off after landing. Tom Blundell takes one hand off the handle and pushes it towards cover for one.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell gets right behind the line and blocks.
The second new ball has been taken now...
Really good fielding! Fuller and on middle, this is driven nicely but the man at mid on dives to his left and stops it.
Starts off with a slightly fullish delivery, shapes away a touch from just outside off. Left alone.
The second new ball is due now. South Africa have not taken it immediately. Kagiso Rabada to continue with the old nut for now...
On a length around middle, Tom Blundell uses the angle of the bowler and glances it through square leg for a single.

FOUR! Beautiful shot! Duanne Olivier overpitches outside off, shaping away, Tom Blundell leans into the drive and elegantly strokes it through covers. It slows down as it approaches the fence and Glenton Stuurman tries his best to pull it back but the ball has just enough pace to trickle over the fence.
Around off, on a length, it's defended with an angled bat from the back foot.
Beaten! Duanne Olivier hurls a length ball close to off, Tom Blundell feels for it but the ball moves away late to beat the outside edge.
Another delivery outside off has been left by Tom Blundell.
This one is delivered on a good length but wide outside off, an easy leave for Blundell.

Drinks break.  Finally, South Africa have a good hour's play. They have picked up the wickets of Daryl Mitchell and Henry Nicholls in the afternoon session and have bowled with much better skill and intensity. The second new ball is only one over away now and they would be planning to take it immediately to make more inroads. The lead has reached 184 runs.
On a length and around middle, Colin de Grandhomme sits on the back foot and defends it to the leg side.
Back of a length around off, shaping away a hint, Colin de Grandhomme withdraws his bat away at the last moment.
Another delivery outside off has been allowed through to the keeper.
A touch short and outside off, Colin shoulders arms.
Fractionally short and around off, Colin de Grandhomme goes on his back foot and punches it through cover-point for two.
Short and wide outside off, Colin offers no shot.
Fuller and around off, driven off the front foot to covers.
Kagiso Rabada is back into the attack. 1 for 70 from his 21 overs so far.
Outside off and shaping away, Tom leaves. Called a no ball for overstepping.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
In the zone outside off, left alone.
Shortish and on middle, Colin de Grandhomme goes back and helps it through square leg for three runs.
Around off on a length, defended from the back foot.
Colin de Grandhomme is the new batter.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Certainly, there was a lapse in concentration on Henry Nicholls' part after reaching his century and he has eventually fallen. Duanne Olivier speeds in and angles across a full-length ball outside off, at 132.6 kph, the invitation is there to drive and Henry Nicholls falls into the trap. A bit loose from him as he gets forward and edges it towards Aiden Markram at second slip who makes no mistake. A timely breakthrough for South Africa with the second new ball just around the corner. Anyway, a fantastic knock by Henry. Lead is 178 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Aiden Markram b Duanne Olivier

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, around off and angling in, Tom Blundell goes on the back foot and defends it to mid-wicket.
Delivers it on a good length around off, Blundell defends it off his back foot.
Nicholls does the same. Goes on the back foot and plays it with soft hands to covers for one. These are annoying runs for South Africa. And...it's a no ball too for overstepping.
Around off, on a length, Blundell gets forward and drops it with gentle hands to covers for a quick run.
Back of a length around middle, Tom shuffles across and plays it down in front of leg slip.
Short and around off, tapped down to covers for one.
Bumper around leg, Henry Nicholls sits underneath it.
Gets forward and pushes a full ball to covers.
Bowls it on a length an wide outside off, Tom leaves.
Around the pads, it's eased in front of square leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Loose! Loss in concentration, perhaps. Short and wide outside off, Henry flashes and misses.

FOUR! HUNDRED FOR NICHOLLS! He continues to impress, stands out when his team needs. Has nicely replaced Ross Taylor at four. Very full and outside off, Henry Nicholls reaches out and squeezes it out through backward point for a boundary. Out comes the helmet and up goes the bat as Henry acknowledges the crowd and his teammates in the dressing room. He was a bit edgy last evening but has looked a lot composed today - making full use of those dropped catches.
Duanne Olivier is back into the attack.
In the channel outside off, Tom allows it through to the keeper.

FOUR! Nicely executed! Marco Jansen bangs it in short, around off, Tom Blundell stands tall inside the crease, gets on top of the bounce and intentionally keeps his hook shot all along the ground through square leg for a boundary.
Fuller and around leg, Nicholls nudges it behind square leg for a run. Moves to 98!
Bumper on middle, this time Henry ducks.
Play and a miss! Short in length and outside off, Henry Nicholls steps back to make room and slap it over point but fails to collect. Clearly, he is feeling the heat of the 90s.
Marco Jansen speeds in from 'round the wicket for the left-hander and digs in a short ball around leg, Nicholls ducks.
Lands it full and on off, angling in, Tom Blundell leans forward and defends it watchfully.
Quite wide outside off, on a good length, Tom has nothing to do with it.
A gentle length ball outside off, left alone.

Slightly short and on middle, Tom Blundell turns inside the crease and works it behind square leg for a couple of runs. While turning for the second run, the bat of Tom brushed the right shin of the bowler. Unintentional.
On a length and close to off, Blundell covers the line and offers a dead bat in defense.
Back of a length, around off, Henry goes on the back foot and taps it down to point. He ambles across to the other end and then has to hurry as the fielder fires a throw at the bowler's end.
Targets the off stump with a length delivery, Tom Blundell solidly defends it from the crease.
In the channel outside off, it lands on a length and straightens, Tom Blundell strides forward and allows it through.
Dean Elgar has a quick word with his bowler.
Hurls across a shortish length ball outside off, Tom allows it through.
Leg slip in place. Marco Jansen comes from 'round the wicket...
Short and wide outside off, it's slapped through backward point for a single. Moves to 96!
Good length, on middle, defended to mid on.
FOUR! Edgy, up and over the slip cordon! Short in length and outside off, Nicholls tries to unveil his favourite square cut but it flies off the outside edge over Elgar at first slip for a boundary.
Fuller and closer to off, Blundell draws forward and pushes it defensively to short cover.
Angles in a length ball on off, Tom is on his toes in defense.
In the zone outside off, Blundell is content in leaving it.

FOUR! What a shot! Glenton Stuurman gets just a little straighter, pitches it up and around off, Tom Blundell leans into his drive, transfers his weight superbly and caresses it down the ground for a boundary. Classy!
Fullish and outside off, zipping off the surface, Tom Blundell presses forward and shoulders arms.
Around off on a good length, it's defended off the back foot.
Another delivery outside off to complete the over.
Outside off, in the right channel, it's left alone.

Shout for an lbw! Fuller in length around middle and nipping back in, Henry Nicholls tries to flick but misses. He is pinged on the pads, they appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Marco Jansen turns and starts to go to his mark. Dean Elgar wants to know whether to take the DRS or not but his bowler has turned his back on him. Elgar looks at his keeper who appears to be unsure. Eventually, the referral is not taken. Going down the leg side, confirms the replay.
Marco Jansen goes fuller on this occasion, around off, Henry Nicholls presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Back of a length and close to off, Henry goes on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Fractionally short and around middle, Henry Nicholls glances it off his hips through square leg for a couple of runs. He moves into the 90s.
Good length and on middle, defended. End of another good over from Glenton Stuurman! He has been good after the break.
That is a very good leave! Tom Blundell surely knows where his off pole is. Outside off and it comes back in. Tom Blundell covers his off pole and shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone again.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one. The lead is now 150.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven to mid on.
Excellent running! On the pads, this is worked through square leg. Tom Blundell wants two and gets two.
This one is down the leg side, left alone.
Two is the call and two is what they get! On the pads, this is is nudged around the corner at square leg. Tom Blundell is underway.
Cuts him into half! All of a sudden, the ball has started to play tricks! Back of a length and outside off, this one jags back in sharply. Blundell is cut into half as he tries to block.
That is a brave leave! He left that on length! It lands just outside off and comes back in. Tom Blundell shoulders arms to this one. It goes just over the off pole.
Shorter and on the pads, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.
Probably looks to do that but slips this one down the leg side. Blundell looks to flick but misses. End of a successful over for Glenton Stuurman!
Another one which comes back in from outside off, left alone. Needs to be a little closer to the off pole.

Really good from Glenton Stuurman! Already one can see the difference, he is running in a lot better and finding the correct line and length. This time gets it back in from outside off, not enough though to make the batter play.
He is getting the ball to move nicely! Another outswinger, slightly shorter in length. Tom Blundell initially looks to poke at it but then pulls his bat back.
Tom Blundell walks out to bat!

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! That is a sharp catch and it is the first Test wicket for Glenton Stuurman! Just what he needed, he wasn't up to the mark in the morning session but strikes on his second ball after Lunch. Perfect for him and for the Saffas. Lovely shape on that delivery. It is fuller and on off, shapes away late at 134 clicks. Draws Daryl Mitchell into the drive, he does so but due to the movement, ends up playing inside the line. It flies off the outside edge to first slip where Elgar takes a sharp catch in front of his face. Can this be the start of something for the visitors?
Commentary.Howout: c Dean Elgar b Glenton Stuurman

Commentary.Commentary: Starts off with one on the pads, it is worked through square leg for one. Glenton Stuurman needs to get his line and length correct quickly, he was not upto the mark in the first session.
Who will bowl from the other end then? Glenton Stuurman it is.
Fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell drives to mid off.
